$ Excel: File -> Info -> Check for Issues

table { ll
  Inspect Document ☰
  Check for Accessibility ☰
  Check Compatibility ☰
table }

{ Inspect the Workbook

  Identify the following possibly problematic issues:
  • Document properties, document server properties, content type information, printer path, author's name, related date and absolute path
  • Headers and footers
  • Hidden rows and hidden columns
  • Hidden worksheets
  • Custom XML data
  • PivotTables, PivotCharts, cube formulas, slicers and timelines
  • Macros, forms or ActiveX controls
  • Links to other files
  • Active filters
  • Hidden names
  • Content that people with disabilities are unable to read

}
{ Check Accessibility

  Check the workbook for content that people with disabilities might find difficult to read.

}
{  Check Compatibility

  Check for features not supported by earlier versions of Excel

}

sa:
  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Info[File -> Info]
